<p class="article-lead">The best questions to ask a perfume manufacturer reveal responsibility and evidence, not just price.</p><ul><li>Which steps are performed at your facility and which are outsourced?</li><li>What determines MOQ for my exact package?</li><li>Who owns or may reuse the fragrance formula?</li><li>How are bottle, pump and liquid compatibility checked?</li><li>What must I approve before production?</li><li>Which documents can be supplied for my destination market?</li><li>How is lead time calculated and what starts it?</li><li>What batch and component records support repeat orders?</li><li>How are defects, leakage and transport claims handled?</li></ul><p>Send a real brief and judge the quality of the answers. A supplier willing to identify limitations is usually more useful than one giving immediate unconditional assurances.</p>
